The paper introduces a new model of network creation games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The model involves players with different weights and a critical distance, which suggests a social network analysis perspective (cs.SI, cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the PoA (price of anarchy) of the game, which is a concept in distributed computing and optimization (cs.DM, cs.IT).
